      • filteredIterator

        public static <M,​P> Iterator<M> filteredIterator​(Iterator<M> iterator,
                                                       Predicate<? super M,​P> predicate,
                                                       P p)
        Returns a filtered view of iterator containing only those elements which match predicate. The returned iterator supports element removal via the remove() method subject to any constraints imposed by iterator.
        Type Parameters:
        M - The type of elements contained in iterator.
        P - The type of the additional parameter to the predicate's matches method. Use Void for predicates that do not need an additional parameter.
        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to be filtered.
        predicate - The predicate.
        p - A predicate specified parameter.
        Returns:
        A filtered view of iterator containing only those elements which match predicate.

      • transformedIterator

        public static <M,​N,​E extends RuntimeException> Iterator<N> transformedIterator​(Iterator<M> iterator,
                                                                                           org.forgerock.util.Function<? super M,​? extends N,​E> function)
        Returns a view of iterator whose values have been mapped to elements of type N using function. The returned iterator supports element removal via the remove() method subject to any constraints imposed by iterator.
        Type Parameters:

        N - The type of elements contained in the returned iterator.
        E - The type of the exception thrown by the function.
        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to be transformed.
        function - The function.
        Returns:
        A view of iterator whose values have been mapped to elements of type N using function.

      • unmodifiableIterator

        public static <M> Iterator<M> unmodifiableIterator​(Iterator<M> iterator)
        Returns a read-only view of iterator which does not support element removal via the remove(). Attempts to use the remove() method will result in a UnsupportedOperationException.
        Type Parameters:
        M - The type of elements contained in iterator.
        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to be made read-only.
        Returns:
        A read-only view of iterator which does not support element removal via the remove().
